  "abstract": "By 2025, India’s population is expected to grow to 1.4 billion. Food production in India must\r\nincrease by about five million tons (Mt) annually for the next 25 years to ensure food and\r\nnutritional security. The rainfed areas, which cover almost 70% of the total area under\r\nagriculture, would have a greater share in meeting the future food needs of the country,\r\nespecially those of food legumes. All the three ICRISAT mandate legumes (groundnut,\r\npigeonpea and chickpea) are major sources of protein for the Indian population.\r\n",
